So hopefully people noticed
it in the demo there.

00:26:56.560 --> 00:26:59.240
But one of my favorite features
of the app is on the

00:26:59.240 --> 00:27:01.540
menu screen, like the artist
screen for example.

00:27:01.540 --> 00:27:05.600
You start off with a fully
translucent action bar.

00:27:05.600 --> 00:27:07.930
And then as you scroll down the
content, it fades in the

00:27:07.930 --> 00:27:10.130
background [INAUDIBLE].

00:27:10.130 --> 00:27:12.810
To me, it works brilliant for
making the most of the imagery

00:27:12.810 --> 00:27:14.935
as well as working with
the Action Bar

00:27:14.935 --> 00:27:16.330
pattern very, very flexibly.

00:27:16.330 --> 00:27:19.370
Can you give us some background
on how you came up

00:27:19.370 --> 00:27:25.930
with that or what were your
design goals for that piece?

00:27:25.930 --> 00:27:29.230
OWEN OTTO: I think basically the
idea was we really wanted

00:27:29.230 --> 00:27:35.170
to focus on the imagery, and by
a sort of making the Action

00:27:35.170 --> 00:27:38.210
bar be transparent, it really
made the image pop more and

00:27:38.210 --> 00:27:41.490
more of the centerpiece
of the screen.

00:27:41.490 --> 00:27:44.580
And then I don't remember who
came up with the idea of it

00:27:44.580 --> 00:27:47.250
kind of fading into orange, but
roughly, it was to solve

00:27:47.250 --> 00:27:50.570
the problem of that when you
scrolled down, you needed to

00:27:50.570 --> 00:27:54.730
make sure that you could see the
controls when the picture

00:27:54.730 --> 00:27:56.080
wasn't there anymore.

00:27:56.080 --> 00:27:59.050
And so it just wound up being
kind of a cool touch to solve

00:27:59.050 --> 00:28:00.240
that problem.

00:28:00.240 --> 00:28:01.650
MARCO PAGLIA: Yeah and something
to say about the

00:28:01.650 --> 00:28:03.100
Action bar.

00:28:03.100 --> 00:28:06.330
I think there's a lot of ways
that we can play with Action

00:28:06.330 --> 00:28:10.860
bars to be differentiating
within applications.

00:28:10.860 --> 00:28:13.100
And this is a very
good example.

00:28:13.100 --> 00:28:16.050
And you have a lot of examples
on Android in general.

00:28:16.050 --> 00:28:20.650
So in Play, for instance, we
decided to put a flat icon

00:28:20.650 --> 00:28:22.710
instead of the 3D icon
in the Action bar.

00:28:22.710 --> 00:28:24.900
We made this Action
bar very flashy.

00:28:24.900 --> 00:28:27.800
We kind of invested in them and
we invested in the colors

00:28:27.800 --> 00:28:29.190
that we have.

00:28:29.190 --> 00:28:31.500
At the same time, when you get
to an artist, you kind of feel

00:28:31.500 --> 00:28:32.760
that that is the
artist's page.

00:28:32.760 --> 00:28:35.300
It's not the music page.

00:28:35.300 --> 00:28:36.870
And so it has to belong
to the artist.

00:28:36.870 --> 00:28:38.510
And that's why it has
to feel that it's

00:28:38.510 --> 00:28:40.420
more neutral as possible.

00:28:40.420 --> 00:28:44.830
And like I said before, a lot
of examples on Android today

00:28:44.830 --> 00:28:48.620
about different uses of Action
bar that can make our layout

00:28:48.620 --> 00:28:49.590
very flexible.

00:28:49.590 --> 00:28:52.530
Another example that I can
remember, for example, is the

00:28:52.530 --> 00:28:58.190
agenda view on a calendar on a
phone where the Action bar

00:28:58.190 --> 00:29:01.760
shows one of the items of the
agenda view itself and so it

00:29:01.760 --> 00:29:03.390
shows the information
present in there.

00:29:03.390 --> 00:29:06.100
It doesn't have any
calendar icon.

00:29:06.100 --> 00:29:08.590
And it's just part of
the informational

00:29:08.590 --> 00:29:11.640
structure of the page.

00:29:11.640 --> 00:29:16.900
Same goes with the people
application where in a

00:29:16.900 --> 00:29:17.600
[INAUDIBLE]

00:29:17.600 --> 00:29:20.560
of the people application, the
Action bar takes the name of

00:29:20.560 --> 00:29:24.990
the person and it's not just the
anti-real estate to have

00:29:24.990 --> 00:29:25.790
an app for them.

00:29:25.790 --> 00:29:29.190
So I re-invite everybody to
think about ways that we can

00:29:29.190 --> 00:29:32.300
play with the Action bar but
still keeping it consistent

00:29:32.300 --> 00:29:35.450
because that really
affects usability.

00:29:35.450 --> 00:29:38.090
So it's important to obviously
stick to the patterns.

00:29:41.160 --> 00:29:41.840
NICK BUTCHER: Yeah definitely.

00:29:41.840 --> 00:29:44.265
I think it's one of the best
ways you can bring branding to

00:29:44.265 --> 00:29:44.970
your application as well.

00:29:44.970 --> 00:29:47.730
You have this bar that
[INAUDIBLE].

00:29:47.730 --> 00:29:49.840
I think you've done a really
nice job in the Play app so

00:29:49.840 --> 00:29:54.440
that it's obviously a suite
of very closely--

00:29:54.440 --> 00:29:55.680
like close cousins apps.

00:29:55.680 --> 00:29:57.660
You can tell that they're
designed together in concert,

00:29:57.660 --> 00:29:59.900
but they have their own
personality right through the

00:29:59.900 --> 00:30:01.460
different colors and so forth.

00:30:01.460 --> 00:30:03.770
So I think that's a really nice
use of the Action bar to

00:30:03.770 --> 00:30:05.770
bring that branding to
each individual app.

00:30:05.770 --> 00:30:07.230
MARCO PAGLIA: There's some other
tricks that we made with

00:30:07.230 --> 00:30:09.900
color that you can
pay attention to.

00:30:09.900 --> 00:30:13.530
For example, we have, instead
of affordances like the

00:30:13.530 --> 00:30:18.330
pinning icon and other icons
that change color according to

00:30:18.330 --> 00:30:19.430
the application you're in.

00:30:19.430 --> 00:30:22.120
So on music, everything is
styled to be orange.

00:30:22.120 --> 00:30:24.500
In books, everything is
styled to be blue.

00:30:24.500 --> 00:30:27.700
In magazines, everything
is styled to be purple.

00:30:27.700 --> 00:30:29.690
And same goes even with
the touch feedback.

00:30:29.690 --> 00:30:32.450
If you pay attention to the
music app, the touch feedback

00:30:32.450 --> 00:30:35.890
is actually an orange overlay,
while on the books application

00:30:35.890 --> 00:30:36.595
it's a blue overlay.

00:30:36.595 --> 00:30:38.670
There are a lot of little
touches that we put here and

00:30:38.670 --> 00:30:44.750
there to make each application
to feel very playful but also

00:30:44.750 --> 00:30:49.870
part of the same family.

